{"id": "EUVD-2023-59728", "enisaUuid": "7ac7bb7c-642e-3979-9287-278fc86e0d23", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbpf: Skip task with pid=1 in send_signal_common()\n\nThe following kernel panic can be triggered when a task with pid=1 attaches\na prog that attempts to send killing signal to itself, also see [1] for more\ndetails:\n\n  Kernel panic - not syncing: Attempted to kill init! exitcode=0x0000000b\n  CPU: 3 PID: 1 Comm: systemd Not tainted 6.1.0-09652-g59fe41b5255f #148\n  Call Trace:\n  <TASK>\n  __dump_stack lib/dump_stack.c:88 [inline]\n  dump_stack_lvl+0x100/0x178 lib/dump_stack.c:106\n  panic+0x2c4/0x60f kernel/panic.c:275\n  do_exit.cold+0x63/0xe4 kernel/exit.c:789\n  do_group_exit+0xd4/0x2a0 kernel/exit.c:950\n  get_signal+0x2460/0x2600 kernel/signal.c:2858\n  arch_do_signal_or_restart+0x78/0x5d0 arch/x86/kernel/signal.c:306\n  exit_to_user_mode_loop kernel/entry/common.c:168 [inline]\n  exit_to_user_mode_prepare+0x15f/0x250 kernel/entry/common.c:203\n  __syscall_exit_to_user_mode_work kernel/entry/common.c:285 [inline]\n  syscall_exit_to_user_mode+0x1d/0x50 kernel/entry/common.c:296\n  do_syscall_64+0x44/0xb0 arch/x86/entry/common.c:86\n  entry_SYSCALL_64_after_hwframe+0x63/0xcd\n\nSo skip task with pid=1 in bpf_send_signal_common() to avoid the panic.\n\n  [1] https://lore.kernel.org/bpf/20221222043507.33037-1-sunhao.th@gmail.com", "datePublished": "2025-03-27T18:31:26", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-29T18:30:29", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4923160393b06a34759a11b17930d71e06f396f2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a1c0263f1eb4deee132e11e52ee6982435460d81", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0dfef503133565fa0bcf3268d8eeb5b181191a65", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1283a01b6e19d05f7ed49584ea653947245cd41e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a3d81bc1eaef48e34dd0b9b48eefed9e02a06451", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-52992"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-52992"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "043ff1da-4706-382a-945b-d8e4b05e9b1c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8b401f9ed2441ad9e219953927a842d24ed051fc <1283a01b6e19d05f7ed49584ea653947245cd41e"}, {"id": "1357b21f-295d-375e-8b15-3be7e4a8d1cb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8b401f9ed2441ad9e219953927a842d24ed051fc <4923160393b06a34759a11b17930d71e06f396f2"}, {"id": "24920dfc-23eb-3683-944f-5befc7dc9017", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.92"}, {"id": "32f6cf82-75ef-3d56-8905-da4f75663b45", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.3"}, {"id": "3378c15e-159c-3d1f-aa93-3295ed0bc81b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2"}, {"id": "3393162c-21a3-34f8-956a-32cab6295f0f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8b401f9ed2441ad9e219953927a842d24ed051fc <a3d81bc1eaef48e34dd0b9b48eefed9e02a06451"}, {"id": "4bfdc6d9-2c7a-38cd-bcca-9d5f1ecaad72", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.4.231"}, {"id": "614c4f10-fd03-3dc6-83d2-3b49e1b47efc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <a1c0263f1eb4deee132e11e52ee6982435460d81"}, {"id": "63a8e1e6-efae-3024-826e-1389f66569c6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <0dfef503133565fa0bcf3268d8eeb5b181191a65"}, {"id": "8a49ace1-a5b6-3fe1-8a55-bfa623e73492", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8b401f9ed2441ad9e219953927a842d24ed051fc <a1c0263f1eb4deee132e11e52ee6982435460d81"}, {"id": "b28a54be-e8a4-3f71-8701-2f8e5c743a2d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <4923160393b06a34759a11b17930d71e06f396f2"}, {"id": "b909cec9-f0ca-3a6e-9fcd-07566bc0574e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <a3d81bc1eaef48e34dd0b9b48eefed9e02a06451"}, {"id": "bb6a0bfe-d320-3560-bf81-295eb002c